DAY 2 — PROCESS VS THREAD
------------------------
Introduction
------------
Programs run as processes, and processes contain threads.

Basic Definitions:
-----------------
Process:
--------
Independent program in execution
Has its own memory
Thread:
-------
Smallest unit of execution
Exists inside a process
Shares memory with other threads
  
Differences:
------------
Feature	       Process	  Thread
Memory	       Separate	  Shared
Speed	         Slower	    Faster
Communication	 Difficult	Easy
  
Process States:
---------------
New
Ready
Running
Waiting
Terminated
  
Multithreading Problems:
------------------------
Race Condition
Deadlock
Starvation
Context Switching
Switching CPU between processes/threads
